data.text: fight ♦ clash ♦ brawl ♦ struggle ♦ scuffle ♦ tussle

data.chText: 以上各词均指搏斗、打斗、打架。
data.enText: These are all words for a situation in which people try to defeat each other using physical force.
fight
a situation in which two or more people try to defeat each other using physical force

data.chText: 他在酒吧里和一个男人斗殴。
data.enText: He got into a fight with a man in the bar.
clash

data.chText: 新闻用语，指两群人之间短暂的打斗、打架、冲突：
data.enText: ( journalism ) a short fight between two groups of people

data.chText: 警方与示威者发生了冲突。
data.enText: Clashes broke out between police and demonstrators.
brawl

data.chText: 通常指一群人在公共场合喧闹、斗殴、闹事：
data.enText: a noisy and violent fight involving a group of people, usually in a public place
a drunken brawl in a bar
struggle

data.chText: 指搏斗、扭打，尤指抢夺、挣扎脱身：
data.enText: a fight between two people or groups of people, especially when one of them is trying to escape, or to get sth from the other

data.chText: 在谋杀现场没有搏斗痕迹。
data.enText: There were no signs of a struggle at the murder scene.
scuffle

data.chText: 指短暂而不太激烈的扭打、冲突：
data.enText: a short and not very violent fight or struggle

data.chText: 他和一名摄影记者发生了肢体冲撞。
data.enText: He was involved in a scuffle with a photographer.
tussle

data.chText: 尤指为争夺物品的短时间的扭打、争斗、争执：
data.enText: a short struggle, fight or argument, especially in order to get sth
He was injured during a tussle for the ball.

We clashed over the new farm policies

value.def: When people clash, they fight, argue, or disagree with each other.

example.ex: A group of 400 demonstrators clashed with police...
example.tran: 400名示威者与警察发生了冲突。

example.ex: Behind the scenes, Parsons clashed with almost everyone on the show...
example.tran: 在幕后，帕森斯几乎和剧组的所有人都发生过冲突。

example.ex: The United States and Israel clashed over demands for a UN investigation into the killings.
example.tran: 美国和以色列在要求联合国对屠杀事件开展调查这一问题上意见相左。

example.ex: There have been a number of clashes between police in riot gear and demonstrators.
example.tran: 防暴警察和示威人群已发生多起冲突。

value.tran: 发生冲突;打斗;争论;意见不合

value.def: Beliefs, ideas, or qualities that clash with each other are very different from each other and therefore are opposed.

example.ex: Don't make any policy decisions which clash with official company thinking...
example.tran: 所作的任何决策都不要和公司官方理念相冲突。

example.ex: Here, morality and good sentiments clash headlong.
example.tran: 在这个问题上，道德和良知互不相容。

example.ex: Inside government, there was a clash of views.

value.tran: (信仰、观点、特性)相互冲突，相互抵触，不相容

value.def: If one event clashes with another, the two events happen at the same time so that you cannot attend both of them.

example.ex: The detective changed his holiday dates when his flight was brought forward and it now clashed with the trial.
example.tran: 由于航班提前，侦探更改了度假日期，但是这样一来就和审判冲突了。

value.def: If one colour or style clashes with another, the colours or styles look ugly together. You can also say that two colours or styles clash .

example.ex: The red door clashed with the soft, natural tones of the stone walls...
example.tran: 红门和石墙柔和的自然色调不协调。

example.ex: So what if the colours clashed?
example.tran: 那么，要是色彩不搭怎么办？

value.def: Sports journalists sometimes say that two individuals or teams who compete against each other clash, especially when a lot of feeling is involved.

example.ex: Lewis has recently recovered his fitness and will clash with Christie in the 4x100m relay...
example.tran: 刘易斯近来恢复了状态，将在4×100米接力赛中和克里斯蒂一决雌雄。

example.ex: The two sides will clash there only if Chelsea beat Sunderland in their quarter-final replay.
example.tran: 只有切尔西队在四分之一决赛的重赛中击败桑德兰队，双方才会交锋。

example.ex: Australia's rugby union team for the return clash with New Zealand is weakened by injury.
example.tran: 将再次和新西兰队交手的澳大利亚业余英式橄榄球队由于球员受伤实力削弱了。

value.tran: (体育用语中尤用来指热情高涨的比赛双方)交锋，交手，厮杀

value.def: When metal objects clash, they make a lot of noise by being hit together.

example.ex: The golden bangles on her arms clashed and jingled.
example.tran: 她手臂上的金手镯丁零当啷地响。

example.ex: ...a noise like the clash of cymbals.

value.tran: (金属相互碰撞)发出当啷当啷声，发出撞击声
